main event: Two white objects were observed in the sky over Pasco, Washington, on June 6, 1954.
interesting points: The sighting lasted for 2 minutes,The objects were observed at an elevation of approximately 30 degrees,The objects disappeared slowly into the dark,The observation was made from a distance of 3.8 miles from Pasco,The source of the report is linked to Project Blue Book.
witness description: single observer from a distance of 3.8 miles
